Spain’s Telecoms Regulator Freezes Fixed Phone Rates for 2012

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-09-29T06:57:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/spain-s-telecoms-regulator-freezes-fixed-phone-rates-for-2012.html
Spain ’s telecommunications market
commission froze the charge consumers pay every month to rent
fixed telephone lines at 13.97 euros, the regulator said in an
e-mailed statement today.  Those charges generated 2.75 billion euros of revenue in
2010 for telecoms operators, the regulator, known as CMT, said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Manuel Baigorri at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net  